Any obstacle or delay in a given effort could trigger a new and devastating attack on financial markets.
The Italian Foreign Bank Association joined the pressure and warns that Monti's failure could be a disaster.
Monti began negotiations with political parties, trade unions and business groups, youth and women's organisations on Monday.
The round closes on Tuesday night.
Monti was appointed on Sunday by President Napolitan, who allowed a very rapid procedure in response to the crisis.
