Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical tests
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized in a public hospital on Tuesday, where he will be tested for muscle loss suffered in the lower limbs area, informed by his attending physician.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed by his government (1990 - 2000), suffers from several diseases, including language cancer, for which he has been operated four times and has already been controlled by doctors.
A member of Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, told television station Canal N that Fujimori will be undergoing tests within three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases, where they should find out why he hurts and why he loses strength in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga said that in his opinion Fujimori might receive a pardon for humanitarian reasons, however, the former president himself does not want a pardon because he feels innocent.
He was operated four times due to tongue cancer, dropped 18 kilograms, and other disorders such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreatic cyst, kidney stones, high pressure and circulatory problems in his legs were added to these problems, and the doctor named them.
Fujimori has served his sentence since September 2007 at the National Directorate of Special Police Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 persons killed by a murdering squadron of troops acting illegally in the early years of his reign.
