There was an eviction of an occupied house in which giant parties were held
Intruders appropriated 11 of the 13 apartments in the building in Balmes, 51
12 occupiers left the house yesterday at noon without resisting
All indications are that the nightmare experienced by the number 51 neighbors on Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building at noon yesterday, illegally residing and organized giant parties that woke the neighbors, leaving the building under court orders without having to interfere with the police.
After the operation was completed, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent a recurrence of the situation.
"From now on, the entrance will be guarded", said the warden.
Occupants who took up 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the remaining ones are inhabited - took away all electrical and partly water equipment, in addition they painted walls and left behind garbage of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
Huge parties took place in the first three apartments, which lasted up to two days and awakened other tenants.
Next to the building is a disco, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained for Europa Press that while the building was occupied, the revenues fell by 80%.
The owner of the disco emphasizes that the occupations of the building made her unfair competition because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while the disco costs 10.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment company had to respond to the neighbors' noise lawsuits. However, the problems were not caused by discos, but by residents of the occupied house and especially by those who took part in the organized parties, whose frequency and intensity has increased in recent weeks, according to the angry inhabitants of the area.
The owner of the disco explained that the problems were so great that they even agreed with the owner of the building and have been forgiving her rent for nine months.
The city police have also confirmed that they have received more complaints from neighbors about the situation in recent weeks.
The chair of the PP People's Party City Hall, Alberto Fernández Díaz, last week demanded that "the building be immediately evicted and thus put an end to the problems of civil coexistence suffered by neighbors and the destruction of the area".
The chair of the People's Party explained that only one floor had been taken a summer ago, but in recent months, the occupying parties had reached all floors of the building and almost all apartments and in one of them there were even thefts.
In this respect, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to be consistent when it comes to acts against civil responsibility that have occurred in the building".
Yesterday, city police also cleared out the building in Nou Barris.
At 15 o'clock 30 minutes, police reached building 35 on Mont-ral Street after being called by neighbors who saw four people entering the building.
All four of them were immediately detained.
Park or mountains?
Architects met on the occasion of a hearing that carries more than controversy over fees
The city tender for 16 gates again opens the debate about the role of Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the time of the greatest bloom of the already defunct Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this self-government printed several pamphlets to support Collserola Park.
The flyer defined the mountain as a large park of metropolitan Barcelona.
More importantly, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with New York Central Park.
After the disappearance of CMB in 1987, the park returned to the mind of many as the top border of Barcelona. The Catalonian capital is one of the few, which is not oriented to the north-south axis, but up (mountain) - down (sea).
Collserola's qualifications as a natural park go this way.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with boars instead of a Yogi bear.
This was the position until September when the City Hall announced a mega competition consisting of 16 auditions for the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
Of course, the gate records the park's idea.
Either this or someone's trying to put the gate in the field.
So there is only one question: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both from a purely organizational point of view and a reflection on the city, this question becomes the central theme of all Barcelona's architects.
It's already a theme as tacky as when two members of this old caste of chosen people shake hands in an elevator meeting.
And it was this act that triggered one of the rare congruents between what three Barcelona architects and preeminent university professors think.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modol, and Marta Bayona: the tender has its merits.
According to Roldan, after the question of the bay side was raised, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain side", so Ildefons Cerd's speech on green apples was not reached to the end.
"We must base ourselves on the principle that the largest park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things, by its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex", said the architect for whom the name "gates to Collserola" carries a "lexicological trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as defining zones where they can be operated".
MODOL, like Roldan and Bayona with experience from the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as a "intellectual challenge" offering "some dangers".
The danger arising from the "insecurity presented today by the public place project" after the experience of the 1980s, which had in the Forum area "its swan singing".
The first concern is the very definition of the boundaries where it should be built.
"Something to define means to take the next step", that is essentially moving on.
"It is necessary to keep in mind new urban and planning tools because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster".
Looking more closely at the question, Modol believes that Collserola's valley slope can be "considered a park", but not the Barcelona part, for purely topographical reasons.
MODOL also recalled that there was already work done by Patronat de Collserola, which "may not end up at the junkyard", although it welcomes the fact that the town hall offers its grémia that it will intervene in the project from "first moment".
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and city is a kind of pass allowing architects to engage in debate, but "doubts", that it should be precisely this technical profile, which will lead multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skills", he adds), which must be created: "Architekti should only be tools".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the name of this game is complex because there is no global vision of Collserol in the tender documentation: "16 tenders have been announced that deal with all the axis of the mountain - the sea, but there is no longitudinal study that looks at the area and understands it as a whole".
This causes at least him to sign up for all 16 tenders.
Otherwise, the project of one gate may refer to the concept and definition of the architect of the neighbouring gate.
In his view, the town hall should guarantee that the zone located immediately above Ronda de Dalt should provide a zone of equipment throughout the length to ensure a smooth transition between the city and greenery.
Casino is pardoned by Jonah Larrazábal, who will be released
After 72 days of imprisonment, legal agent Cadino Red granted pardon to Mayor Monterrey's brother in a trial in which he was prosecuted for alleged blackmail.
Manuel Jonás Larrazábal spent 72 days in prison and will now be released after legal agent Casino Red granted him a pardon in front of the Second Criminal Court in the district, which discussed the blackmail case in which Mayor Monterrey's brother was charged.
After the assassination of Casino Royale, the owner of Casino Red, Sergio Gil García, published a series of photographs and videos on which Manuel Jonás was to ask him to pay an economic quota to allow the Monterrey Town Hall to allow illegal operation in the betting house.
After a public indictment, the State Prosecutor initiated a prosecution of the brother of the Panist mayor. On September 2, he was detained and imprisoned for 30 days.
