The leaders allowed him to stay in San Nicolás de los Garza city cells during the trial.
On October 25, he was presented with an arrest warrant issued by Secretary of the Second Criminal Court, Jorge Yánez, who stated that after nearly two months of investigation sufficient evidence was collected to prove Jonah’s guilt. Evidence includes, for example, the payment of the sum of 1.5 million pesos to casino representatives in exchange for the promise that the operation would be made possible.
This Monday, the legal agent of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, came to Judge José Luis Pecino and asked for mercy for the region's mayor's brother, on the basis of which he will soon be able to return to freedom.
